<subSubSection id="2BBF6525FF8F4017A8BCB47BFBDAFB95" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="631A36AEFF8F4017A8BCB47BFA0CFEB4" blockId="3.[192,1440,349,1111]" box="[192,1434,349,374]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A8BCB47BFEE1FEB7" bold="true" box="[192,375,349,374]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<typeStatus id="BC1E880CFF8F4017A8BCB47BFE92FEB4" box="[192,260,350,374]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A902B478FCEEFEB4" authority="Walsingham, 1891" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1891" box="[382,888,349,374]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conchylis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacteipalpis">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A902B478FD1FFEB7" box="[382,649,349,373]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Conchylis lacteipalpis</emphasis>
Walsingham, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation (Walsingham 1914).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="631A36AEFF8F4017A894B45BFB26FCF5" blockId="3.[192,1440,349,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
The precise circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AA14B458FD67FE57" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[616,753,381,405]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017AA14B458FD67FE57" box="[616,753,381,405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its putative synonyms (see 
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017ACF5B45BFAB6FE57" author="Brown, J. W." box="[1161,1312,381,405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref5281" refString="Brown, J. W. 2005. World catalogue of insects. Volume 5: Tortricidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo Books; Stenstrup, Denmark. 741 p." type="book" year="2005">Brown 2005</bibRefCitation>
) has been somewhat elusive owing to the absence of an abdomen of the 
<typeStatus id="BC1E880CFF8F4017ABCEB4BBFB8CFE74" box="[946,1050,414,438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">holotype</typeStatus>
of the type species of the genus (i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A886B498FD95FE17" authority="Sodovsky, 1837" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1891" box="[250,515,445,469]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conchylis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacteipalpis">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A886B498FD95FE17" box="[250,515,445,469]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Conchylis lacteipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). As currently defined, the genus is anchored by species that are superficially similar to its type species and assigned to the genus by Walsingham (1914). The most convincing morphological autapomorphy for 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A989B4DBFDE8FDD4" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[501,638,510,534]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A989B4DBFDE8FDD4" box="[501,638,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the conspicuous Y- or T-shaped median process of the transtilla, which easily separates males from those of all other Cochylina. Razowski (1994) identified the following as putative autapomorphies for the genus: a tooth-like process of the vinculum (highly variable and not always present); a sclerotized pocket at the base of the valva (usually present); an expanded apex of the median process of the transtilla (mentioned above, always present); and the presence of a subterminal prominence of the phallus (absent in many species). Also, males of some species of 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017ACAEB7BBFACDFD74" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[1234,1371,670,694]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017ACAEB7BBFACDFD74" box="[1234,1371,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have secondary structures from the venter of the abdomen. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AB89B79BFA36FD14" authority="Walsingham, 1914" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[1013,1440,702,726]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multistrigata">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017AB89B79BFB20FD14" box="[1013,1206,702,726]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">S. multistrigata</emphasis>
Walsingham, 1914
</taxonomicName>
has a small bilobed process on abdominal segment 7 from which a pair of laterally directed hairpencils originate. Similar structures are reported and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017ABD7B7DBFA94FCD5" author="Razowski, J. &amp; V. O. Becker" box="[939,1282,766,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="421 - 464" refId="ref5947" refString="Razowski, J., and V. O. Becker. 1983. Brazilian Cochylidii (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia 26: 421 - 464." type="journal article" year="1983">Razowski and Becker (1983</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3, 21) in 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A8BCB63BFD56FCF5" authority="Razowski and Becker, 1983" authorityName="Razowski and Becker" authorityYear="1983" box="[192,704,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nauphraga">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A8BCB63BFEFEFCF4" box="[192,360,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">S. nauphraga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017A913B63BFD56FCF5" author="Razowski, J. &amp; V. O. Becker" box="[367,704,798,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="421 - 464" refId="ref5947" refString="Razowski, J., and V. O. Becker. 1983. Brazilian Cochylidii (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia 26: 421 - 464." type="journal article" year="1983">Razowski and Becker, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AA80B63BFB3BFCF5" authority="Razowski and Becker, 1983" authorityName="Razowski and Becker" authorityYear="1983" box="[764,1197,798,823]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ficta">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017AA80B63BFCC4FCF4" box="[764,850,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">S. ficta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017AB25B63BFB3BFCF5" author="Razowski, J. &amp; V. O. Becker" box="[857,1197,798,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="421 - 464" refId="ref5947" refString="Razowski, J., and V. O. Becker. 1983. Brazilian Cochylidii (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia 26: 421 - 464." type="journal article" year="1983">Razowski and Becker, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="631A36AEFF8F4017A894B61BFA99FC15" blockId="3.[192,1440,349,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
Based on morphological features, primarily the dorso-posteriorly directed socii, 
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017ACA9B61BFA0DFC94" author="Razowski, J." box="[1237,1435,830,854]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="55 - 60" refId="ref5840" refString="Razowski, J. 1985. On the generic groups Saphenista and Cochylis (Tortricidae). Nota Lepidopterologica 8 (1): 55 - 60." type="journal article" year="1985">Razowski (1985</bibRefCitation>
, 1994) concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A9BAB67BFDD9FCB4" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[454,591,862,886]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A9BAB67BFDD9FCB4" box="[454,591,862,886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AB3BB67BFC59FCB4" authorityName="Le Marchand" authorityYear="1933" box="[839,975,862,886]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017AB3BB67BFC59FCB4" box="[839,975,862,886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Phalonidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and a recent phylogenetic analysis of the subtribe (
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017A91FB65AFDADFC55" author="Brown, J. W. &amp; L. Aarvik &amp; M. Heikkila &amp; R. L. Brown &amp; M. Mutanen" box="[355,571,895,919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref5312" refString="Brown, J. W., L. Aarvik, M. Heikkila, R. L. Brown, and M. Mutanen. 2019. Molecular phylogeny of Cochylina, with confirmation of its relationship to Euliina (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Systematic Entomology 45: doi: 10.1111 / syen. 12385." type="book" year="2019">Brown et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
) provides some support for this conclusion, although in the latter study 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A8BCB6BBFEDFFC74" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[192,329,926,950]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A8BCB6BBFEDFFC74" box="[192,329,926,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(+ 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A909B6BBFD39FC75" authority="Meyrick, 1917" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1917" box="[373,687,926,951]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Amallectis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A909B6BBFE60FC74" box="[373,502,926,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Amallectis</emphasis>
Meyrick, 1917
</taxonomicName>
) was recognized as one of six major lineages in the subtribe Cochylina, sister to the 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A99EB69BFDFCFC14" authorityName="Le Marchand" authorityYear="1933" box="[482,618,958,982]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A99EB69BFDFCFC14" box="[482,618,958,982]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Phalonidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group + the 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AB71B69BFCE2FC14" authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1829" box="[781,884,958,982]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017AB71B69BFCE2FC14" box="[781,884,958,982]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Cochylis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017AC5AB69AFA94FC15" author="Brown, J. W. &amp; L. Aarvik &amp; M. Heikkila &amp; R. L. Brown &amp; M. Mutanen" box="[1062,1282,959,983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref5312" refString="Brown, J. W., L. Aarvik, M. Heikkila, R. L. Brown, and M. Mutanen. 2019. Molecular phylogeny of Cochylina, with confirmation of its relationship to Euliina (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Systematic Entomology 45: doi: 10.1111 / syen. 12385." type="book" year="2019">Brown et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="631A36AEFF8F4017A894B6FAFBDAFB95" blockId="3.[192,1440,349,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
Adults of 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017A921B6FBFE70FC34" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[349,486,990,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017A921B6FBFE70FC34" box="[349,486,990,1014]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are highly variable in maculation and size (i.e., forewing length). Males lack a forewing costal fold, and most (but not all) species have a hindwing costal roll (hair pencil), the last feature shared with most “advanced” 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AA53B13AFC37FBF5" authority="(Brown et al. 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Brown" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[559,929,1055,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Cochylina (
<bibRefCitation id="07344B5FFF8F4017AAC6B13AFC0FFBF5" author="Brown, J. W. &amp; L. Aarvik &amp; M. Heikkila &amp; R. L. Brown &amp; M. Mutanen" box="[698,921,1055,1079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref5312" refString="Brown, J. W., L. Aarvik, M. Heikkila, R. L. Brown, and M. Mutanen. 2019. Molecular phylogeny of Cochylina, with confirmation of its relationship to Euliina (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Systematic Entomology 45: doi: 10.1111 / syen. 12385." type="book" year="2019">Brown et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In contrast, females of many 
<taxonomicName id="A4A54D2DFF8F4017AD6AB13AFA09FBF5" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1914" box="[1302,1439,1055,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Saphenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51D1EABCFF8F4017AD6AB13AFA09FBF5" box="[1302,1439,1055,1079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Saphenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species retain the plesiomorphic condition of three spines in the frenulum.
</paragraph>
